<paragraph blockId="5.[151,883,1231,1258]" box="[151,883,1231,1258]" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,883,1231,1258]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,883,1231,1258]" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">
<taxonomicName box="[151,296,1231,1257]" class="Gastropoda" family="Mangeliidae" genus="Bela" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="nebula">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,296,1231,1257]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">Bela nebula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<typeStatus box="[303,431,1232,1258]" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">Lectotype</typeStatus>
: implications for 
<taxonomicName box="[650,705,1231,1257]" class="Gastropoda" family="Mangeliidae" genus="Bela" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[650,705,1231,1257]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">Bela</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[767,883,1231,1257]" class="Gastropoda" family="Mangeliidae" genus="Mangelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[767,883,1231,1257]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">Mangelia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1302,2011]" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">
Although the number of species included in the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[777,828,1302,1327]" class="Gastropoda" family="Mangeliidae" genus="Bela" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[777,828,1302,1327]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">Bela</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been drastically reduced during the last decades, 
<taxonomicName box="[151,203,1338,1363]" class="Gastropoda" family="Mangeliidae" genus="Bela" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,203,1338,1363]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">Bela</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may still represent several distinct genus-level groups. Doubts on its monophyly have been expressed, in particular concerning 
<taxonomicName authority="Philippi, 1844" authorityName="Philippi" authorityYear="1844" box="[397,846,1374,1399]" class="Gastropoda" family="Turridae" genus="Pleurotoma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="brachystoma">
<emphasis box="[397,680,1374,1399]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">Pleurotoma brachystoma</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Philippi" box="[687,846,1374,1399]" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" refString="Philippi, R. A. (1844) Enumeratio Molluscorum Siciliae cum Viventium tum in Tellure Tertiaria Fossilium quae in Itinere suo Observavit Auctor. Volumen Secundum Continens Addenda et Emendanda, nec non Comparationem Faunae Recentis Siciliae cum Faunis Aliarum Terrarum et cum Fauna Periodi Tertiariae. E. Anton, Halis Saxonum, iv + 303 pp." type="book" year="1844">
Philippi, 
<number box="[790,846,1375,1399]" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" value="1844.0">1844</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and related species (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Mariottini" box="[1125,1368,1374,1399]" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" refString="Mariottini, P., Di Giulio, A., Smriglio, C. &amp; Oliverio, M. (2008) Notes on the Bela brachystoma complex, with description of a new species (Mollusca, Gastropoda,; Conidae). Aldrovandia, 4, 3 - 20." type="journal article" year="2008">
Mariottini 
<emphasis box="[1246,1303,1374,1399]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">et al.</emphasis>
2008
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Mariottini" box="[1380,1436,1375,1399]" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" refString="Mariottini, P., Smriglio, C., Di Giulio, A. &amp; Oliverio, M. (2009) A new fossil conoidean from the Pliocene of Italy with comments on the Bela menkhorsti complex (Gastropoda: Conidae). Journal of Conchology, 40, 5 - 14." type="journal article" year="2009">2009</bibRefCitation>
for further details). The species illustrated in figures 
<number box="[739,752,1411,1435]" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" value="2.0">2</number>
A–I and 
<number box="[850,863,1411,1435]" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" value="2.0">2</number>
M– 
<collectingCountry box="[904,924,1411,1435]" name="Iceland" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">O</collectingCountry>
give an idea of the broad morphological shell variability seen in the genus 
<emphasis box="[472,530,1446,1471]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">
<taxonomicName box="[472,526,1446,1471]" class="Gastropoda" family="Mangeliidae" genus="Bela" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">Bela</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
as currently conceived.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1302,2011]" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">
The designation of a 
<typeStatus box="[451,553,1482,1507]" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">lectotype</typeStatus>
for 
<taxonomicName box="[608,719,1482,1507]" class="Gastropoda" family="Mangeliidae" genus="Bela" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="nebula">
<emphasis box="[608,719,1482,1507]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">B. nebula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
allows closer constraint on the usage of 
<taxonomicName authority="Leach" authorityName="Leach" box="[1206,1337,1482,1507]" class="Gastropoda" family="Mangeliidae" genus="Bela" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1206,1258,1482,1507]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">Bela</emphasis>
Leach
</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation author="Gray" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" refString="Gray, J. E. (1847 a) The classification of the British Mollusca, by W. E. Leach, M. D. Annals and Magazine of Natural History, 20, 267 - 273. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1080 / 037454809496042" type="journal article" year="1847" yearSuffix="a">
Gray (
<number box="[159,219,1519,1543]" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" value="1847.0">1847</number>
a)
</bibRefCitation>
. The genus 
<taxonomicName box="[387,439,1518,1543]" class="Gastropoda" family="Mangeliidae" genus="Bela" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[387,439,1518,1543]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">Bela</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should include species with small shells (commonly shell height &lt;
<quantity box="[1242,1317,1518,1543]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" unit="mm" value="15.0">15mm</quantity>
), with the protoconch nucleus smooth; if multispiral (i.e., whorls&gt; 
<number box="[796,812,1555,1579]" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" value="2.0">2</number>
), the protoconch whorls are smooth, except for the last where low, curved axial riblets are overrun by a few rows of obsolete spiral elements forming swollen tubercles at the intersection. Micropustules are sometimes present, especially in proximity to the protoconch-teleoconch junction. The teleoconch is generally fusiform with the spire whorls of slight to medium convexity, hence giving the spire a conical profile. Sutures are commonly bordered by a subsutural, slightly swollen collar. On the teleoconch, the axial sculpture is predominant and extending between the sutures, whereas the numerous spiral elements are subdued and commonly interrupted by dense growth lines. In addition, dense micropustules cover the remaining teleoconch surface. The aperture is lanceolate, elongated, with a thin outer lip smooth inside. The siphonal canal is short and the anal sinus is shallow and placed on the subsutural ramp. Examples of species we consider belonging to 
<taxonomicName box="[414,466,1878,1903]" class="Gastropoda" family="Mangeliidae" genus="Bela" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[414,466,1878,1903]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">Bela</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are: 
<taxonomicName authority="Pallary 1904" authorityName="Pallary" authorityYear="1904" box="[531,936,1878,1903]" class="Gastropoda" family="Mangeliidae" genus="Ginnania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="taprurensis">
<emphasis box="[531,775,1879,1902]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">Ginnania taprurensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Pallary" box="[786,936,1878,1903]" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" refString="Pallary, P. (1904) Addition a la faune malacologique du Golfe de Gabes. Journal de Conchyliologie, 52, 212 - 248. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 13040" type="journal article" year="1904">
Pallary 
<number box="[877,936,1879,1903]" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" value="1904.0">1904</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<taxonomicName authority="Deshayes 1835 sensu Nordsieck (1977)" authorityName="Deshayes 1835 sensu Nordsieck" authorityYear="1977" class="Gastropoda" family="Turridae" genus="Pleurotoma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="fuscata">
<emphasis box="[952,1176,1878,1903]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">Pleurotoma fuscata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Deshayes" box="[1187,1362,1878,1903]" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" refString="Deshayes, G. P. (1835) Expedition Scientifique de Moree. Vol. 3. Mollusques. Bertrand, Paris, 123 pp. [pp. 81 - 203]" type="book chapter" year="1835">
Deshayes 
<number box="[1306,1362,1878,1903]" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" value="1835.0">1835</number>
</bibRefCitation>
<emphasis box="[1374,1436,1879,1902]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">sensu</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Nordsieck" box="[151,356,1914,1939]" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" refString="Nordsieck, F. (1977) The Turridae of the European Seas. La Piramide, Rome, 131 pp." type="book" year="1977">
Nordsieck (
<number box="[289,348,1915,1939]" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" value="1977.0">1977</number>
