<figureCitation box="[676,745,1484,1509]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1856,1878]" captionTargetBox="[240,1356,195,1838]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[240,1357,195,1839]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Optical microscope photos of teleoconch features; scale bars 1 mm. A – C) Bela fuscata (Deshayes, 1835) sensu Nordsieck (1977), from Punta Ala (Grosseto, Italy). D) Bela brachystoma (Philippi, 1844) from Djerba (Tunisia), and (F – G) from Porto Azzurro (Leghorn, Italy). G – I) † Bela hispidula (Bellardi, 1847) from Formello Quarry (Rome, Italy). J – L) Mangelia striolata Risso, 1826 from Procida Island (Naples, Italy). SEM photos of protoconch features; scale bar 0.1 mm. M) B. fuscata from Punta Pioppeto (Naples, Italy). N) B. brachystoma from Elba Island (Grosseto, Italy). O) † B. hispidula from Ca’ Lametta (Bologna, Italy). P) M. striolata from Djerba (Tunisia). Symbol: † fossil." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/287444/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">
Fig. 
<number box="[730,745,1484,1508]" pageId="6" pageNumber="51" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
