<figureCitation box="[272,344,1519,1544]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1839,1861]" captionTargetBox="[237,1287,339,1815]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[237,1349,339,1815]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Optical microscope and scanning electron microscope (SEM) photos of Bela nebula (Montagu 1803); scale bars 1 mm and 0.1 mm, respectively. A – C lectotype,  Exem: Moll 4253 / 5; D – F topotype,  NMW 1953.183.02275 / 1; G – K topotype  NMW 1953.183.02276 / 1; L topotype  NMW 1953.183.02281 / 1. Topotype specimens from Torbay, Devon (UK).  shell number in Table 1." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/287443/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">
Figs. 
<number box="[334,344,1520,1544]" pageId="6" pageNumber="51" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
J–L; 
<number box="[405,420,1520,1544]" pageId="6" pageNumber="51" value="2.0">2</number>
M). Anatomical features for 
